I did not answer the question about gender because I don't have one. I am a woman, an adult human female. I resent being forced to participate in the religion of gender identity, which I do not believe in, by only having the choice of 'genders’ to pick from, without there being an option state my sex. Once again, I have NO gender identity, I do not believe in any such thing, and I don't ‘identify' with anything. I believe in biological and material reality. Your data will not be useful as you will not be able to disaggregate by sex, and if you don't understand why this is important you ought to read Invisible Women by Caroline Criado Perez. At the very least you should ask about sex (that is natal, biological, factual) in addition to what people might imagine or wish themselves to be. My sex, being a woman, is not a feeling or an identity, it is a material fact.
